{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55c3e075-47eb-469c-bf4f-15dbd00dea69","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed before it.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_EwVat5lTZP3IQxf3QwrsNA","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-783cdfcd122344e3a7156180ef0b0317/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-783cdfcd122344e3a7156180ef0b0317/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"7198a30c-82e6-40b4-bdcd-ef61a3cfc28d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` is listed first but it depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). Similarly, `Program.fs` depends on both `Domain.fs` and `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (no dependencies)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on Domain and Services)\n\nSo I need to reorder the compile entries in the project file to match this dependency chain.","outputTokens":471,"requestId":"1C3F:2E56AC:B20BFB:CED88B:69F3FA0D"},"id":"ef2ae8a0-b0cd-4085-963d-4c239420e407","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:49.369Z","parentId":"11e5fb79-0378-49c2-a2b6-03746e5d079c"}
